 a BS necklace MADE by any jeweler that has better stats than this amulet, why would we even bother to wear it?<br><br>Alas, it's sitting in my bank collecting dust and I'm very disappointed.<br><br>I'm hoping someone will revisit the stats on this piece. It's definitely not even worth the time or money I spent getting it.<br><br>Rhiana Mistweaver<br>Brell<br>Silent Redemption<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugherad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gherad</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/10/00 11:03:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PoA Wizard Quest - Amulet of Planar Transferance</span><hr size=1> Is there some way to recharge the amulet?  A single charge of the spell is absurd.  I have trouble believing that even the geniuses at Verant could consider that a good item.  Anyone who could complete that quest would have items with far better stats than that.  There must be someway to use it more than once. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urhiana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhiana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/10/00 12:14:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://veranon.dhs.org/img/rhiana.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PoA Wizard Quest - Amulet of Planar Tra